M: I think instead of 24. Kg2 it would have been better to take on a6. Kg2 gives me the chance to indirectly protect the pawn on a6 with Rd5. After Rd5 the pawn on a6 is "poisoned".

M: This take on a6 costs you the quality (N for a P) and opens the a-file for my rook!!! Maybe activating your h-rook would have been a rout to go (25. Rhf1 or 25. Rhe1).
